Much attention has been given to the impact of informativeness and similarity measures on distributional thesauri . <S>
We investigate the effects of context filters on thesaurus quality 
and propose the use of cooccurrence frequency as a simple and inexpensive criterion . <S>
For evaluation , we measure thesaurus agreement with WordNet and performance 
in answering TOEFL-like questions . <S>
Results illustrate the sensitivity of distributional thesauri to filters . <S>
